{"flatpakAppId":"com.github.akiraux.akira","name":"Akira","summary":"The Linux Design Tool","description":"\n    <p>\n      A modern UX Design Application for UI and UX Designers\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      ⚠ WARNING! Akira is still under development and not ready for production. Missing features, random bugs, and black\nholes opening in your kitchen are to be expected.</p>\n    <p>\n      Akira is a native Linux Design application built in Vala and Gtk. Akira focuses on offering a modern and fast approach\nto UI and UX Design, mainly targeting web and graphic designers. The main goal is to offer a valid and professional solution for designers who want to use Linux as their main OS.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      Features Include:\n    </p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Fully vector canvas for infinite resizing without quality loss</li>\n      <li>Smart option panel that shows the editable features of a selected item</li>\n      <li>Layers panel with easy Drag and Drop and smart ordering</li>\n      <li>Create Artboards to better organize your design iterations and views</li>\n      <li>Control the size and quality of exported images</li>\n      <li>Customizable icon set</li>\n      <li>And so much more…</li>\n    </ul>\n  ","developerName":null,"projectLicense":"GPL-3.0+","homepageUrl":"https://github.com/akiraux/akira","donationUrl":"https://www.paypal.me/alecaddd","translateUrl":null,"bugtrackerUrl":"https://github.com/akiraux/akira/issues","helpUrl":"https://github.com/akiraux/akira/issues","categories":[{"name":"Utility"},{"name":"Graphics"}],"downloadFlatpakRefUrl":"akira","currentReleaseVersion":"0.0.16","currentReleaseDescription":null,"iconDesktopUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble/com/github/akiraux.akira/16f2fed70458cddcd8da424ad9c32b92/icons/128x128/akira_com.github.akiraux.akira.png","iconMobileUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble/com/github/akiraux.akira/16f2fed70458cddcd8da424ad9c32b92/icons/128x128/akira_com.github.akiraux.akira.png","screenshot